.TH "ice_devlink_devcaps_snapshot" 9 "ice_devlink_devcaps_snapshot" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ice_devlink_devcaps_snapshot \- Capture snapshot of device capabilities
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ice_devlink_devcaps_snapshot
.BI "(struct devlink *devlink "  ","
.BI "const struct devlink_region_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "struct netlink_ext_ack *extack "  ","
.BI "u8 **data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "devlink" 12
the devlink instance
.IP "ops" 12
the devlink region being snapshotted
.IP "extack" 12
extended ACK response structure
.IP "data" 12
on exit points to snapshot data buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is called in response to the DEVLINK_CMD_REGION_TRIGGER for
the device-caps devlink region. It captures a snapshot of the device
capabilities reported by firmware.

\fIreturns\fP zero on success, and updates the data pointer. Returns a non-zero
error code on failure.
